  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "To manage worksite and Construction based project Project",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2><p>We are seeking a <strong>Site Engineer / Project Engineer</strong> to manage and coordinate construction works on site, ensuring projects are delivered safely, on time, and in compliance with Singapore regulations and approved drawings.</p><p>The successful candidate will work closely with project managers, subcontractors, consultants, and regulatory authorities to ensure smooth site operations and quality execution.<br /></p><h2><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Oversee daily <strong>site operations</strong> and construction activities</p></li><li><p>Ensure works are carried out according to <strong>approved drawings, specifications, and method statements</strong></p></li><li><p>Coordinate with <strong>subcontractors, suppliers, and consultants</strong></p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with <strong>BCA, MOM, NEA, and other statutory requirements</strong></p></li><li><p>Monitor project progress, manpower deployment, and material usage</p></li><li><p>Conduct <strong>site inspections</strong> and ensure quality standards are met</p></li><li><p>Enforce <strong>workplace safety and health (WSH)</strong> practices at all times</p></li><li><p>Prepare and submit <strong>site reports, progress updates, and documentation</strong></p></li><li><p>Attend site meetings and resolve technical or coordination issues</p></li><li><p>Assist in project planning, scheduling, and cost control where required<br /></p><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ul><li><p>Diploma or Degree in <strong>Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or related field</strong></p></li><li><p>Minimum <strong>2–5 years of relevant construction site experience</strong> in Singapore (preferred)</p></li><li><p>Familiar with <strong>Singapore construction regulations and codes of practice</strong></p></li><li><p>Able to read and interpret construction drawings and specifications</p></li><li><p>Good coordination, problem-solving, and communication skills</p></li><li><p>Strong sense of responsibility, integrity, and teamwork</p></li><li><p>Proficient in Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook)</p></li><li><p>Candidates with <strong>WSH certificates</strong> will be an advantage</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
